snippet.textDisplay: Zariya is a masterpiece. Who really understand music, they'll agree on it. And somebody has said A R Rahman's music has too much influence of Western Music. For them I'll say, he allows all the influence from the entire world. He is equally strong in both eastern and western music. Numerous Eastern compositions he has already offered to us. There will be some criticism always. All great men have some number of critics. Hence he has some. But that never stopped him from winning him so many international awards and acclaim including Grammy and Oscar.

snippet.textDisplay: Bravo!!! I can't get enough off of listening this ("Zaria") although I didn't understand most of the lyrics. However, A.R. has done an amazing job, I love his great sense of music composition. He nailed it and took this tune to a different level by mixing three different tunes. I love when Ani brings peace and harmony to elevate our inner Zen; chorus singers added soothing chorus flawlessly. As far as Farah's soulful voice goes, she forced me to ask myself, who am I and why I am here for? While I linger on that deep thought, she quickly turned me exquisitely harmonious and put smile on my face. Finally, well-done all the musicians, who've worked hard for this fine piece of art work.
